-- Russian conglomerate Sistema Q2 net profit down 3.7 pct
-- By Maria Kiselyova
-- Thu Aug 28, 2014 03:13AM EDT
-- None



MOSCOW, Aug 28 (Reuters) - Russian oil-to-telecoms conglomerate Sistema <SSAq.L> <AFKS.MM> said on Thursday its second-quarter net profit fell 3.7 percent, year-on-year, due to a one-off gain a year ago.

Sistema, whose biggest assets are majority stakes in Russia's top mobile operator MTS <MBT.N> and mid-sized oil firm Bashneft <BANE.MM>, reported a net profit of $509.6 million, down from $529.1 million a year ago but up 47.7 percent compared to the year-ago net profit adjusted for the one-off gain.